      "side": 1,
      "message": "For the Inliner case, yeah it\u0027s always something that would pass IsTrivialExpression and is an lvalue. (In no case would `y\u003dx` make sense to pass to UpdateRefKind because y and x shouldn\u0027t have the same refkind :)  )\n\nI suppose for the simplifyExpression +\u003d case, you could have something bizarre on the left like \n\n(x, y) +\u003d 0\n\n?\nAt any rate, this is tricky enough that I think I am going to stop relying on IsAssignable and probably copy the implementation from the Inliner (which used a ProgramWriter to just burrow through the entire expression)",
